    "content_hash": "714a61cb9972f119",
    "department": "Engineering",
    "description": "Tempo is a layer-1 blockchain purpose-built for stablecoins and real-world payments, born from Stripe’s experience in global payments and Paradigm’s expertise in crypto tech.\n\nTempo’s payment-first design provides a scalable, low-cost predictable backbone that meets the needs of high-volume payment use cases. Our goal is to move money reliably, cheaply, and at scale. Our north star is simplicity for users: fintechs, traditional banks, merchants, platforms, and anyone else looking to move their payments into the 21st century.\n\nWe're building Tempo with design partners who are global leaders in AI, e-commerce, and financial services: Anthropic, Coupang, Deutsche Bank, DoorDash, Mercury, Nubank, OpenAI, Revolut, Shopify, Standard Chartered, Visa, and more.\n\nWe’re a team of crypto-optimists, building the infrastructure needed to bring real, substantial economic flows onchain. We like to move fast and swing for the fences — join us!\n\nThe Role\n\nYou’ll help put the Tempo blockchain in the hands of real users. That happens in two ways: building first-party products like Tempo Wallet, and working directly with customers to integrate Tempo into their stablecoin flows. You’ll work closely with production grade blockchain systems, money movement flows.\n\nThis role is a strong fit for a former founder, or someone who wants to start a company one day. You’ll get exposure to a wide range of business-critical payments and crypto problems across startups, mid-market companies, and enterprises. You’ll move between building products and deploying them inside customer environments, gaining a deep understanding of the full product, integration, and go-to-market cycle.\n\nResponsibilities\n\n - Build internal and first-party applications on top of Tempo for both agents and humans\n\n - Partner with startups and enterprises to integrate Tempo into their payment systems\n\n - Develop a deep understanding of the Tempo blockchain and its product surface area\n\n - Navigate unfamiliar codebases and organizations quickly to get products shipped\n\n - Bring field learnings back to Tempo to improve the product, developer experience, and blockchain itself\n\nQualifications\n\n - 4+ years of full-stack engineering experience, including 1+ year(s) in crypto\n\n - Strong communication skills and the ability to work across technical and cross-functional stakeholders\n\n - Ability to travel within the US to work with partners when needed\n\n - Track record of shipping mission-critical systems where safety and reliability matter\n\n - Ability to balance speed, pragmatism, and technical quality\n\nAttributes\n\n - High motor\n\n - Razor-sharp thinker with precise command of language\n\n - Concise, evidence-based communicator\n\n - Excellent organizational and logistical skills\n\n - Intense curiosity and open-mindedness\n\n - Scrappiness; willingness to roll up sleeves",
